    <text id="R12948967T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate General Jubal Early announces his intentions to move to Staunton in
                    late December, 1863. Early prepared to meet a Union advance, probably in
                    conjunction with Union General William Averell's raid into West Virginia and the
                    Shenandoah Valley.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Colonel JACKSON or Colonel ARNETT:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-12-20">December 20, 1863.</date>
                        <name type="place">MILLBOROUGH,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>I am leaving here for Staunton with General Thomas' brigade. I am compelled to go
                    there to meet a force coming up the valley. I should have been too late to do
                    anything by going to Warm Springs and Gatewood's. I could not cross streams. I
                    could not get a force to you for same reason. Do the best you can. Telegraph to
                    me at Staunton. Fitzhugh Lee encamped near Fincastle last night.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>J. A. EARLY,<lb/> Major-General.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
